    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A Scottish term for laced shoes made out of the untanned hide of an animal, with the hair facing to the outside; molded to the foot when the hide is still pliant.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
